overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  which included a database, API endpoints, and report generation. I conducted a
  thorough analysis against the provided Statement of Work and detailed
  questionnaire specification, identifying both well-implemented features and
  significant gaps. High-priority missing items included a tiredness severity
  scale with safety messaging, explicit COMISA detection, outbound links in
  reports, insufficient sleep syndrome detection, and weighted EDS scoring.
  Following the user's approval, I began implementing the plan. I successfully
  integrated a 1-10 tiredness severity scale into the questionnaire UI, complete
  with a critical safety warning for scores indicating high risk. Additionally,
  I implemented logic to detect Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  incorporated specific recommendations for this condition into both the
  web-based report and the downloadable PDF. The conversation concluded with
  these two high-priority items addressed, with further enhancements pending.
